The CyberTip contained 1 reported child pornography file. S/Tpr Cooke reviewed the reported child pornography files and determined that it constitutes child pornography as it is defined under Maryland law. The file is described below:

 

Filename: P1GbZ7yMeZiHWBta404139193_2524560724368266_8421058147289945554_n.mp4

Description: 1 minute video file showing an adult female being vaginally penetrated by a juvenile male's penis. The male is reasonably believed to be between 7 - 9 years of age based on lack of development, lack of pubic hair, and overall size compared to the adult female.

 

The CyberTip indicated that the following IP address 2601:c8:8200:51c0:39ed:92a:dd24:ba7 (11-21-2023 03:06:13 UTC) was utilized to upload the reported contraband file.

 

S/T Cooke conducted a query of the upload IP address through an open-source database and determined that it is registered through Comcast Cable and geo-locates generally to Duluth, Georgia.
